sentences: He wrote "Something in the Air" (1969) for the band, which reached No. 1 in the UK Singles Chart.
He played early on with such bands as The Krewsaders, The Second Thoughts (1964–65, with Patrick Campbell-Lyons and Chris Thomas) and The Eccentrics.
Keen's first recorded song was "Club of Lights", recorded in 1966 for Reaction Records by Oscar (Paul Nicholas).
He wrote "Armenia City in the Sky", which was included on the album The Who Sell Out (1967).
Keen died of heart failure in March 2002, seventeen days before his 57th birthday.
